metadata.documentation: Operations and objects for transcribing speech to text.

GetTranscriptionJob.documentation: Returns information about a transcription job. To see the status of the job, check the Status field. If the status is COMPLETE, the job is finished and you can find the results at the location specified in the TranscriptionFileUri field.

exceptions.documentation: There is a problem with one of the input fields. Check the S3 bucket name, make sure that the job name is not a duplicate, and confirm that you are using the correct file format. Then resend your request.
Either you have sent too many requests or your input file is longer than 2 hours. Wait before you resend your request, or use a smaller file and resend the request.
There was an internal error. Check the error message and try your request again.
We can't find the requested job. Check the job name and try your request again.

ListTranscriptionJobs.documentation: Lists transcription jobs with the specified status.

exceptions.documentation: There is a problem with one of the input fields. Check the S3 bucket name, make sure that the job name is not a duplicate, and confirm that you are using the correct file format. Then resend your request.

StartTranscriptionJob.documentation: Starts an asynchronous job to transcribe speech to text.

exceptions.documentation: There is a problem with one of the input fields. Check the S3 bucket name, make sure that the job name is not a duplicate, and confirm that you are using the correct file format. Then resend your request.

BadRequestException.documentation: There is a problem with one of the input fields. Check the S3 bucket name, make sure that the job name is not a duplicate, and confirm that you are using the correct file format. Then resend your request.

ConflictException.documentation: The JobName field is a duplicate of a previously entered job name. Resend your request with a different name.
